context: Miami is the southern terminus of Amtrak's Atlantic Coast services, running two lines, the <a0_0><b5_0>Silver Meteor<b5_0/><a0_0/> and the Silver Star, both terminating in <a1_0><b6_0>New York City<b6_0/><a1_0/>. The Miami Amtrak Station is located in the suburb of <a2_0><b7_0>Hialeah<b7_0/><a2_0/> near the Tri-Rail/Metrorail Station on NW 79 St and NW 38 Ave. Current construction of the Miami Central Station will move all Amtrak operations from its current out-of-the-way location to a centralized location with Metrorail, MIA Mover, Tri-Rail, Miami International Airport, and the Miami Intermodal Center all within the same station closer to Downtown. The station was expected to be completed by <a3_0><b8_0>2012<b8_0/><a3_0/>, but experienced several delays and was later expected to be completed in late <a4_0><b9_0>2014<b9_0/><a4_0/>, again pushed back to early 2015.
